"{\"uid\": \"citizen.co.za-sport-sa-team-deliver-six-medals-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Home\\u00bbSport  ByWesley Botton  Chief sports journalist  3 minute read  12 August 2024  06:20 am  Tatjana Smith secured two medals in the swimming pool at the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21, \"end\": 27, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\", \"score\": 0.901131173431149, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Botton\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botton,_North_Yorkshire\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Picture: Jack Guez/AFP  Heading into the Paris Olympics, the SA team's medal chances looked to be few and far between, and while they did not achieve a record haul at the showpiece which concluded on Sunday, they did well to secure six podium places.\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 422, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 233, \"end\": 235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.428519636165129e-17, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some performances were predicted in advance, with the likes of Tatjana Smith, Alan Hatherly and the men's 4x100m sprint relay team living up to the hype.\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 502, \"end\": 515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"score\": 0.9999924602050241, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alan Hatherly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alan_Hatherly\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were also surprises, however, with javelin thrower Jo-Ane van Dyk delivering the performance of her life and the Blitzboks finding some long-awaited form.\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 636, \"end\": 650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jo-Ane van Dyk\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jo-Ane_van_Dyk\"}, {\"begin\": 698, \"end\": 707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Blitzboks\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Smith was the star of the show, and while she did not win gold in her favoured 200m breaststroke event, sheheld on for silverafter producing a superb performance to win gold in the 100m breaststroke.\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 940, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Having made history as South Africa's most decorated Olympian with four career medals (two gold and two silver), Smith announced her retirement at her peak.\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 965, \"end\": 977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999958518692071, \"rank\": 4.06315009769747e-06, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}, {\"begin\": 995, \"end\": 1003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999805140762, \"rank\": 1.9485845568878488e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the track, after missing out by 0.01 in the men's 100m final, there was relief for consistent sprinter Akani Simbine as heearned an elusive Olympic medal, anchoring a young 4x100m relay squad to silver and a new national record (37.57 seconds).\", \"from\": 1100, \"to\": 1347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1206, \"end\": 1219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Akani Simbine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Akani_Simbine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hatherly was equally impressive in the men's mountain bike cross country race,digging deep to claim bronzeafter a hard-fought contest.\", \"from\": 1349, \"to\": 1483, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And the Blitzboks produced a stunning result.\", \"from\": 1485, \"to\": 1530, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After struggling to qualify for the showpiece, they beat Australia in thebronze medal playoffof the men's rugby sevens tournament.\", \"from\": 1531, \"to\": 1661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1588, \"end\": 1597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9999472368568114, \"rank\": 2.921758514596707e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Van Dyk's result was also a surprise.\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1700, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After setting a personal best of 64.22m in the qualifying round, shelaunched a 63.93m throwin the women's javelin final to grab silver.\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There was some disappointment too, with a few medal contenders missing out, including Pieter Coetze in the swimming pool and the national men's 4x400m relay team on the track.\", \"from\": 1838, \"to\": 2013, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even in those events, however, national records were broken along the way.\", \"from\": 2014, \"to\": 2088, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Coetze finished fifth and seventh in the 100m (52.58) and 200m (1:55.60) backstroke finals respectively, but he broke the African records in both events, while the 4x400m relay team (Gardeo Isaacs, Zakithi Nene, Lythe Pillay and Antonie Matthys Nortje) also set a new SA mark of 2:58.12 to finish fifth in their final.\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2296, \"end\": 2300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Nene\", \"score\": 0.9998399397848944, \"rank\": 0.00016008583868613258, \"text\": \"Nene\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Nene\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Nene\"}, {\"begin\": 2327, \"end\": 2334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Matthys\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthys\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Matthys\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tim_Matthys\"}, {\"begin\": 2358, \"end\": 2360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.428519636165129e-17, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All-in-all, the national team's performance in the French capital was as good as could have been expected, and it was a significant improvement on the all-round effort at the Tokyo Olympics in 2021 where the SA squad earned only three medals.\", \"from\": 2410, \"to\": 2652, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2461, \"end\": 2467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6351948138581238, \"rank\": 0.3163747613278884, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2618, \"end\": 2620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.428519636165129e-17, \"text\": \"SA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And with multiple rising stars sticking up their hands with impressive results in various sports, the future looks bright.\", \"from\": 2654, \"to\": 2776, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They delivered more than expected at theParis Games, and if the nation's elite athletes continue on their upward trajectory, the 2028 Olympics in Los Angeles should be even better.\", \"from\": 2778, \"to\": 2958, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2924, \"end\": 2935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999941654311578, \"rank\": 5.83403845276831e-06, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Add The Citizen as a Preferred Source on Google and follow us on Google News to see more of our trusted reporting in Google News and Top Stories.\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 3105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3001, \"end\": 3007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"score\": 0.9815541137719974, \"rank\": 0.01878763525197346, \"text\": \"Google\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google\"}, {\"begin\": 3025, \"end\": 3036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google News\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\"}, {\"begin\": 3077, \"end\": 3088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google News\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Download our app  Get the latest news and updates on Whatsapp  The latest news directly in your inbox  Support Local Journalism  2026 The Citizen.\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3160, \"end\": 3168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Whatsapp\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WhatsApp\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 3254, \"to\": 3274, \"entities\": []}]}"